This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on March 23, 2018, in celebration of Greek Independence Day. The proclamation highlights the historical and cultural connections between the United States and Greece, emphasizing the shared commitment to liberty and democratic institutions. It mentions the visit of Greek Prime Minister Alexis Tsipras to the White House, the strategic cooperation between the two nations on various issues, and Greece's fulfillment of its NATO obligations. The article also mentions the expansion of economic and commercial ties between the two countries, with the United States serving as the honored country at the 2018 Thessaloniki International Fair. Additionally, it acknowledges the 70th anniversary of Fulbright Greece, an educational and cultural exchange program between the two countries. The proclamation concludes by honoring the Greek-American community and recognizing Greece as a valued partner in promoting peace, liberty, and prosperity globally. As a result, March 25, 2018, is proclaimed as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy.